metadata.name: The car, the violin and the dog Klyaksa.
metadata.description: In my childhood there was a film created by the great director Rolan Bykov. It was called "The car, the violin and the dog Klyaksa. Everything that is good and real that is in us is created in childhood and accompanies us all our lives. This picture is dedicated to my childhood and the film made by a brilliant director who made films for children and teenagers. The picture is painted with acrylic paints on canvas. Size: 120x65 cm. A digital copy of the painting is also available. Size 14173x7677px. 300dpi. 120x65 cm. The printable file is available via a private link.
